                            <comment id="12541148" author="hossman" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 21:57:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW I&apos;m in favor of making a separate PingRequestHandler, but i think we should take advantage of this oportunity to eliminate the use of core.getPingQueryRequest() 9and the horrible syntax it depends on)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This new handler should use it&apos;s own init params to drive the query.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12541151" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 22:01:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;agreed - i&apos;ll post a modified patch shortly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12541166" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 22:44:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated your patch to use its own parameters for the ping query.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also @Deprecated getPingQueryRequest() and removed it from the example solrconfig.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This configures the PingRequestHandler with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;requestHandler name=&quot;/admin/ping&quot; class=&quot;PingRequestHandler&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;lst name=&quot;defaults&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;str name=&quot;qt&quot;&amp;gt;standard&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;str name=&quot;q&quot;&amp;gt;solrpingquery&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;str name=&quot;echoParams&quot;&amp;gt;all&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/lst&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/requestHandler&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This path overrides the ping.jsp servlet and uses the new request handler.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12541418" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 9 Nov 2007 19:35:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks Karsten&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
